00:38:15.840 --> 00:38:18.630
And I think it's a
perfect example of where

00:38:18.630 --> 00:38:20.950
we are in a sense,
because on the one hand,

00:38:20.950 --> 00:38:24.110
we have a world that should
be open for incredible

00:38:24.110 --> 00:38:28.060
possibilities, as you said,
a world in which seemingly

00:38:28.060 --> 00:38:30.510
endless number of paths
are available to us.

00:38:30.510 --> 00:38:34.070
And yet the chilling thing if
one takes these ideas seriously

00:38:34.070 --> 00:38:38.460
is how in practice, we can
so imprison and constrain

00:38:38.460 --> 00:38:40.690
ourselves in terms of that work.

00:38:40.690 --> 00:38:43.710
So getting back to the
key of your question,

00:38:43.710 --> 00:38:46.880
they would argue if it's
true that the world seems

00:38:46.880 --> 00:38:51.040
to us incredibly open, why do
we not live our lives that way?

00:38:51.040 --> 00:38:53.536
And why on the contrary
are we not pursuing

00:38:53.536 --> 00:38:55.660
all these possibilities
that are really potentially

00:38:55.660 --> 00:38:57.960
available to us, but
on the contrary falling

00:38:57.960 --> 00:39:00.612
into these incredibly
dangerous ruts?

00:39:00.612 --> 00:39:02.570
And I would say that's
true of us individually,

00:39:02.570 --> 00:39:05.580
but I would put it in a
larger social level too.

00:39:05.580 --> 00:39:08.390
We live in a world that
is becoming unbelievably

00:39:08.390 --> 00:39:11.990
stratified, where people's
lives are unbelievably-- not

00:39:11.990 --> 00:39:13.940
only routinized,
but actually held

00:39:13.940 --> 00:39:16.980
into certain
socioeconomic positions,

00:39:16.980 --> 00:39:19.240
and are surprisingly
unchangeable.

00:39:19.240 --> 00:39:22.630
So given what would seem
to be the reality of a very

00:39:22.630 --> 00:39:25.830
open world, and equally
the reality of a world

00:39:25.830 --> 00:39:30.130
that we seem to be creating
isn't going on, why not?

00:39:30.130 --> 00:39:32.660
And going back to their
ideas, they would say, well,

00:39:32.660 --> 00:39:35.100
it comes down to the ways
that we live our lives,

00:39:35.100 --> 00:39:38.120
and at a larger level,
the kind of social worlds

00:39:38.120 --> 00:39:40.260
that we've accordingly
created, which we now

00:39:40.260 --> 00:39:42.900
think of as grand and
liberatory, but ironically

00:39:42.900 --> 00:39:45.000
are creating a
completely different type

00:39:45.000 --> 00:39:48.352
of world, which surprisingly
we don't even seem to notice.

00:39:48.352 --> 00:39:50.080
So thank you,
wonderful question.

00:39:50.080 --> 00:39:51.410
Thank you.

00:39:51.410 --> 00:39:52.590
Yes please.

00:39:52.590 --> 00:39:55.010
AUDIENCE: First of all
I'd like to apologize

00:39:55.010 --> 00:39:57.306
on behalf of the site for
