00:39:57.306 --> 00:39:59.740
MICHAEL PUETT: That is fine.

00:39:59.740 --> 00:40:01.960
AUDIENCE: There is one
aspect of finding yourself

00:40:01.960 --> 00:40:03.900
that it strikes me
still has value,

00:40:03.900 --> 00:40:07.350
and that is we have
different values.

00:40:07.350 --> 00:40:09.240
And so finding your
values, not necessarily

00:40:09.240 --> 00:40:13.700
what makes you feel
good, but what you feel

00:40:13.700 --> 00:40:16.560
detracts from you if you
were to turn against it.

00:40:16.560 --> 00:40:19.010
For example, if you value
the helping of others

00:40:19.010 --> 00:40:23.990
and you only pursue wealth, for
reasons other than donation,

00:40:23.990 --> 00:40:27.190
then you are not being
true to your values.

00:40:27.190 --> 00:40:32.510
And that is, I think,
worthwhile to pay attention to.

00:40:32.510 --> 00:40:38.510
But I agree that the find
yourself seems to often mean

00:40:38.510 --> 00:40:40.752
the self in the sense of
wanting to escape from

00:40:40.752 --> 00:40:42.460
rather than the self
in the sense of what

00:40:42.460 --> 00:40:44.460
values are fundamental to me.

00:40:44.460 --> 00:40:46.510
MICHAEL PUETT: Yes,
perfectly put, and I actually

00:40:46.510 --> 00:40:47.820
agree completely.

00:40:47.820 --> 00:40:52.790
So were we to conceptualize the
self in the sense of the self

00:40:52.790 --> 00:40:54.970
that we are creating
through the little works

00:40:54.970 --> 00:40:57.690
that we're doing
all the time, then

00:40:57.690 --> 00:41:00.057
I think the notion of
finding a self works great.

00:41:00.057 --> 00:41:01.890
In other words, finding
a self in that sense

00:41:01.890 --> 00:41:04.630
would be an active
constructive process of,

00:41:04.630 --> 00:41:06.990
as you said, developing
the values that we

00:41:06.990 --> 00:41:08.930
want to be guiding our lives.

00:41:08.930 --> 00:41:11.190
The danger, as you
said, is so often when

00:41:11.190 --> 00:41:13.662
we use the term finding
ourself, we are using it

00:41:13.662 --> 00:41:14.620
in that opposite sense.

00:41:14.620 --> 00:41:18.430
We're using the sense of, I need
to find my true authentic self

00:41:18.430 --> 00:41:21.350
that I should just embrace
and love for who I am.

00:41:21.350 --> 00:41:24.600
And the problem is in
practice, even if we say,

00:41:24.600 --> 00:41:26.590
and part of that is
I'm the sort of person

00:41:26.590 --> 00:41:29.510
who values certain
things, danger

00:41:29.510 --> 00:41:31.850
is with that way of
thinking, actually the way

00:41:31.850 --> 00:41:33.876
we live in our
daily lives perhaps

00:41:33.876 --> 00:41:35.750
is not at all according
to the values that we

00:41:35.750 --> 00:41:38.610
like to think we hold,
that in fact the daily ways

00:41:38.610 --> 00:41:40.610
we're living and the ways
we're affecting others

00:41:40.610 --> 00:41:42.990
can often directly
contradict what

00:41:42.990 --> 00:41:44.964
we claim to be our own values.

00:41:44.964 --> 00:41:46.880
So getting back to the
heart of your question,

00:41:46.880 --> 00:41:50.400
yes, if we can think of the self
as something we are working on,

00:41:50.400 --> 00:41:53.010
constructing, and the values
of the self being something

00:41:53.010 --> 00:41:55.440
that we as human
beings are constructing

00:41:55.440 --> 00:41:58.230
through our daily life and
therefore hopefully embodying

00:41:58.230 --> 00:42:01.850
in the way we live, then it's
a wonderful notion of the self.

00:42:01.850 --> 00:42:04.270
Sadly, it tends to be not
the vision of the self

00:42:04.270 --> 00:42:07.780
that we tend to think about when
we're actually living nowadays.

00:42:07.780 --> 00:42:09.380
AUDIENCE: It's a
form of surrender

00:42:09.380 --> 00:42:12.854
to love the self you have rather
than the self you aspire to.

00:42:12.854 --> 00:42:15.270
MICHAEL PUETT: Yeah, that's
perfectly put-- perfectly put.

00:42:15.270 --> 00:42:19.490
I mean, this sounds so great
to love myself, embrace myself.

00:42:19.490 --> 00:42:21.600
But the danger exactly
as you said is,

00:42:21.600 --> 00:42:24.890
well no, you're just embracing
the set of patterns and ruts

00:42:24.890 --> 00:42:26.060
I've fallen into.

00:42:26.060 --> 00:42:27.910
And the goal should
be aspirational.

00:42:27.910 --> 00:42:31.230
It's to create a great
self, a great self that

00:42:31.230 --> 00:42:34.320
can work well in the world
and help those around one.

00:42:34.320 --> 00:42:36.330
And that's the
vision of self I fear

00:42:36.330 --> 00:42:40.390
we're losing, precisely with
our vision of always being

00:42:40.390 --> 00:42:42.197
true to yourself and
sincere to yourself

00:42:42.197 --> 00:42:43.280
and authentic to yourself.

00:42:43.280 --> 00:42:47.240
Ironically, we're creating the
exact opposite type of a world.

00:42:47.240 --> 00:42:48.210
Great, thank you.

00:42:48.210 --> 00:42:49.150
Thank you.

00:42:49.150 --> 00:42:50.040
Please, yes.

00:42:50.040 --> 00:42:51.320
AUDIENCE: Hi.

00:42:51.320 --> 00:42:53.040
At the end you have
