00:43:33.790 --> 00:43:36.450
in my own house
that I can control,

00:43:36.450 --> 00:43:41.160
because you ultimately can't
control the other bundles.

00:43:41.160 --> 00:43:46.550
I guess sort of how do you
take that jump from hermit

00:43:46.550 --> 00:43:48.780
to joyousness?

00:43:48.780 --> 00:43:50.785
MICHAEL PUETT: Yeah, no,
it's a great question.

00:43:50.785 --> 00:43:53.410
And what they would say-- and I
would agree with them on this--

00:43:53.410 --> 00:43:57.100
is that doing the approach
of sort of locking oneself

00:43:57.100 --> 00:43:59.666
in one's room and not
interacting with others

00:43:59.666 --> 00:44:01.040
in the long run
is actually going

00:44:01.040 --> 00:44:03.420
to be completely
disruptive, that really

00:44:03.420 --> 00:44:05.155
the only way to work
on these patterns

00:44:05.155 --> 00:44:07.890
and ruts is through
interactions.

00:44:07.890 --> 00:44:12.030
And yes, the simple fact-- and I
think you're right about this--

00:44:12.030 --> 00:44:13.619
that so many of our
patterns and ruts

00:44:13.619 --> 00:44:15.160
are formed with what
other people are

00:44:15.160 --> 00:44:17.970
doing around us, who are
equally patterned and rutted.

00:44:17.970 --> 00:44:20.160
The key is what we're
training ourselves

00:44:20.160 --> 00:44:24.242
to do is both act in ways that
hopefully will break patterns

00:44:24.242 --> 00:44:26.770
and ruts with those
around us, but we're also

00:44:26.770 --> 00:44:28.455
training ourselves
not to be affected

00:44:28.455 --> 00:44:31.710
in the same dangerous
ways, they would put it,

00:44:31.710 --> 00:44:33.230
by those around us as well.

00:44:33.230 --> 00:44:34.660
So we turn to that example.

00:44:34.660 --> 00:44:36.720
If that person is
yelling at me, that

00:44:36.720 --> 00:44:39.525
will draw out even someone
who's not yelling but using

00:44:39.525 --> 00:44:40.900
a tone of voice
that for whatever

00:44:40.900 --> 00:44:45.270
reason emotionally reminds me of
someone who used to yell at me.

00:44:45.270 --> 00:44:47.540
That would draw a
certain response.

00:44:47.540 --> 00:44:49.610
So part of the
training exercise is

00:44:49.610 --> 00:44:51.874
you're training yourself
not to passively

00:44:51.874 --> 00:44:53.290
respond that way--
in other words,

00:44:53.290 --> 00:44:56.230
not to respond by those
same patterns and ruts.

00:44:56.230 --> 00:44:58.320
And when that person
does something,

00:44:58.320 --> 00:45:01.590
you're training yourself
not to be so affected by it.

00:45:01.590 --> 00:45:04.810
And in the long run what you
really train yourself to do

00:45:04.810 --> 00:45:07.890
is the next step too, which
is to realize probably

00:45:07.890 --> 00:45:11.320
if that person is doing
something like either yelling

00:45:11.320 --> 00:45:13.070
or some kind of
strong kind of voice,

00:45:13.070 --> 00:45:15.150
it probably is coming
as well from something

00:45:15.150 --> 00:45:17.762
you're doing too--
unconsciously.

00:45:17.762 --> 00:45:19.970
You're just playing out your
usual patterns and ruts.

00:45:19.970 --> 00:45:21.652
But that's creating
the situation

00:45:21.652 --> 00:45:22.860
where that person gets angry.

00:45:22.860 --> 00:45:24.400
You get angry in return.

00:45:24.400 --> 00:45:25.827
You're doing something too.

00:45:25.827 --> 00:45:27.910
And so you're training
yourself not to be affected

00:45:27.910 --> 00:45:29.500
by that person in that way.

00:45:29.500 --> 00:45:32.062
But you ultimately
want to train yourself

00:45:32.062 --> 00:45:33.895
to be able to act in
ways that will actually

00:45:33.895 --> 00:45:35.410
shift that person too.

00:45:35.410 --> 00:45:37.890
So that person's
anger isn't arising,

00:45:37.890 --> 00:45:39.690
it's then generating your anger.

00:45:39.690 --> 00:45:42.850
And that sounds incredibly
difficult, and it is,

00:45:42.850 --> 00:45:45.660
but the key is it can
only be done in practice.

00:45:45.660 --> 00:45:47.650
So you don't want to
sit out in your room

00:45:47.650 --> 00:45:50.040
and think that's
the way to avoid all

00:45:50.040 --> 00:45:51.710
these difficult relationships.

00:45:51.710 --> 00:45:54.680
No, it's only by working on
these difficult relationships

00:45:54.680 --> 00:45:58.170
all the time that you train
yourself both to respond well

00:45:58.170 --> 00:46:00.034
to others, but
again, respond well

00:46:00.034 --> 00:46:01.450
in this strong
sense of responding

00:46:01.450 --> 00:46:04.066
in ways that will bring out
better sides of them as well.

00:46:04.066 --> 00:46:04.720
So great.

00:46:04.720 --> 00:46:06.340
Thank you.

00:46:06.340 --> 00:46:07.540
